SimGrid
------------------------------------------
SimGrid is a scientific instrument to study the behavior of large-scale
distributed systems such as Grids, Clouds, HPC or P2P systems. It can be used
to evaluate heuristics, prototype applications or even assess legacy MPI
applications.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-4.1.10-4
  cygwin-1.7.17-1
  libcgraph6-2.30.0-1
  libgcc1-4.5.3-3
  libpcre1-8.32-1
  perl-5.14.2-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.23.51-1
  cmake-2.8.9-2
  cygport-0.11.3-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-3
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  http://simgrid.gforge.inria.fr/

Canonical download:
  http://gforge.inria.fr/frs/download.php/32047/SimGrid-3.9.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack SimGrid-3.9-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
         unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./SimGrid-3.9-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/SimGrid-3.9-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/SimGrid-3.9-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libsimgrid3.9-3.9-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libsimgrid-devel-3.9-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

